# Project: Resume Tailor
Stack: React + Tailwind (client/), Node.js/Express (server/)
Auth: Clerk (@clerk/clerk-react client, @clerk/clerk-sdk-node server middleware)
Payments: LemonSqueezy (hosted checkout + webhooks at POST /webhooks/lemonsqueezy)
DB: PostgreSQL via pg library
AI: Anthropic SDK, model claude-sonnet-4-6 (override via ANTHROPIC_MODEL)

Rules:
- Never hardcode API keys or secrets. Use process.env.* always.
- All user input must be sanitized before DB insertion. Use parameterized queries ($1, $2 syntax).
- LemonSqueezy webhook route uses express.raw() and must be registered BEFORE express.json()
- Always validate file uploads: check mimetype, enforce 5MB limit via multer
- Rate limit middleware runs before business logic on tailor route
- Never expose internal error messages to the client. Log internally, return generic message.
- Use async/await, not .then() chains
- Every DB query uses parameterized statements. No string concatenation in SQL.
- Never expose LEMONSQUEEZY_API_KEY to the frontend
